{"questionId":"25372264","questionHtml":"<p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A2)</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;into <strong>their</strong> derivative<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0M0A0</strong></em> in cases where candidate’s incorrect derivative is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25372264","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.2","subjectId":"50-dp-